race.comment: Race drops away quickly. QUEENOFTHEAIR (7) resumes for a new yard. Ran a solid race over a mile in Listed grade two back and returns here well back in class. Has placed fresh and can hit the ground running for new stable. MRS PENNY CRACKER (4) was placed two back at the provincials then got off the mark when heavily bet at Haildon. This tougher but one of the few in form and can measure up again. ARTILLERY (1) resumes from a long break. Has the ability and fitter for two trials should run a forward race. SMOKIN' EYES (5) is going better than it looks. Ran fifth in a hot form race last time and is ready to peak after three runs in.  EXPLICABLE (2) changed yard recently and kicked off for the new stable perhaps on the way back home from Victoria with a placing in the country. Well travelled galloper who has won at the trip and is a top three hope.
